TRUSTABLE-SOFTWARE: This
release of JSON-Library
also referred in the
documentation as nlohmann/json
library is Trustable.

TT-EXPECTATIONS: Documentation
is provided within eclipse-score/inc_nlohmann_json,
specifying what the nlohmann/json
library is expected to
do, and what it must
not do, and how this
is verified.

WFJ-02: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library checks the well-formedness
of strings.

NJF-07: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library accepts and rejects
strings according to
RFC8259 ยง7.

NJF-07.1: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept empty
strings.

NJF-07.2: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
the improperly bounded
strings.

NJF-07.3: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
unescaped control characters.

NJF-07.4: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept escaped
control characters.

NJF-07.5: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library accepts UTF-16
surrogate pairs.

NJF-07.6: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept non-empty
strings.

NJF-07.7: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
escaped invalid characters.

NJF-07.8: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
single unpaired utf-16
surrogates.

NJF-07.9: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
unescaped UTF-16 surrogate
pairs.

TA-BEHAVIOURS: Expected
or required behaviours
for the nlohmann/json
library are identified,
specified, verified and
validated based on analysis.
